Job Title: iOS Engineer
About ASOS Technology

We're at the heart of ASOS, delivering innovative technology solutions that drive customer experience.
Job Description

We're expanding our Mobile Development team and seeking a skilled iOS Engineer to join our Customer Experience team. The successful candidate will contribute to the development and maintenance of our iPhone and iPad app, used by over 8 million active users worldwide.

The ideal candidate will have:
• Strong coding knowledge in Swift 5 and foundational iOS frameworks;
• Experience with Xcode, IB, and Auto Layout for creating advanced UIs;
• Deep understanding of Apple's Human Interface Guidelines (HIG) and design best practices;
• Knowledge of software design patterns, architecture principles, and REST API consumption.

You'll be working closely with our design team to implement clean and modern designs that respect the platform. Your proactive approach and hands-on attitude will ensure top-quality projects delivered on time.
What We Offer

As an iOS Engineer at ASOS, you can expect:
• A competitive salary (£60,000 - £80,000 per annum, depending on experience);
• Employee discount (ASOS Develops);
• Personal development opportunities across the business;
• Access to LinkedIn learning materials;
• 25 days paid annual leave + extra celebration day;
• Discretionary bonus scheme;
• Private medical care scheme;
• Flexible benefits allowance.

If you're passionate about iOS development, keen to learn and grow, and want to be part of a dynamic team driving innovation, apply now!
